HEADWORD: Collocution
<hw>Col`lo*cu"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>collocutio</ets>, fr. <ets>colloqui</ets>, <ets>-locutum</ets>, to
converse; <ets>col-</ets> + <ets>loqui</ets> to speak. See
<er>Loquacious</er>.]</ety> <def>A speaking or conversing together;
conference; mutual discourse.</def> <rj><au>Bailey.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

